<div class="section">
  <h2>Selected publications</h2>
  <p class="note">Selected publications are also listed in the complete publication list below.</p>

  <div class="selected">

    <!-- 2024 Vocoded Speech -->
    <div class="sel-item" id="sel-2024-vocoded-speech">
      <p class="sel-citation">
        Mallikarjun, A., Shroads, E., &amp; Newman, R. S. (2024). Perception of vocoded speech in domestic dogs.
        <em>Animal Cognition</em>, 27(1), 34.
      </p>
      <p class="sel-blurb">
        Controlled evaluation of performance under signal degradation to isolate what information is necessary for recognition. Emphasizes robustness, failure modes, and generalization when input quality is systematically degraded.
      </p>
      <div class="links">
        <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DOI</a>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF</a>
        <a href="projects.html#signal-degradation-eval">Project</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 2023 Translational Detection -->
    <div class="sel-item" id="sel-2023-scent-detection-sip">
      <p class="sel-citation">
        Mallikarjun, A., Collins, A., Verta, A., Hanadari-Levy, A., Chaskes, M. B., Rosen, M. R., ... &amp; Otto, C. M. (2023). Canine scent detection of sinonasal-inverted papilloma in blood plasma and nasal secretions.
        <em>Journal of Veterinary Behavior</em>, 62, 29-38.
      </p>
      <p class="sel-blurb">
        End-to-end translational evaluation in a clinically relevant setting, integrating study design, data constraints, and performance analysis. Highlights rigor under real-world operational conditions.
      </p>
      <div class="links">
        <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DOI</a>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF</a>
        <a href="projects.html#translational-detection-evaluation">Project</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 2021 Segmentation -->
    <div class="sel-item" id="sel-2021-segmentation-simulation">
      <p class="sel-citation">
        Tsui, A. S. M., Erickson, L. C., Mallikarjun, A., Thiessen, E. D., &amp; Fennell, C. T. (2021). Dual language statistical word segmentation in infancy: Simulating a language-mixing bilingual environment.
        <em>Developmental Science</em>, 24(3), e13050.
      </p>
      <p class="sel-blurb">
        Empirical and computational framing of learning in mixed, high-variance inputs. Addresses generalization when training and test distributions are not cleanly separated.
      </p>
      <div class="links">
        <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DOI</a>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF</a>
        <a href="projects.html#learning-from-mixed-inputs">Project</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 2019 Cocktail Party -->
    <div class="sel-item" id="sel-2019-cocktail-party-dogs">
      <p class="sel-citation">
        Mallikarjun, A., Shroads, E., &amp; Newman, R. S. (2019). The cocktail party effect in the domestic dog (Canis familiaris).
        <em>Animal Cognition</em>, 22(3), 423-432.
      </p>
      <p class="sel-blurb">
        Study of recognition performance under competing auditory interference, isolating factors that support or degrade selective attention in realistic environments.
      </p>
      <div class="links">
        <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DOI</a>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF</a>
        <a href="projects.html#robustness-in-noise">Project</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 2017 Review (Listed Last) -->
    <div class="sel-item" id="sel-2017-review">
      <p class="sel-citation">
        Mallikarjun, A., Newman, R. S., &amp; Novick, J. M. (2017). Exploiting the interconnected lexicon: Bootstrapping English language learning in young Spanish speakers.
        <em>Translational Issues in Psychological Science</em>, 3(1), 34.
      </p>
      <p class="sel-blurb">
        Review and synthesis comparing psycholinguistic evidence on bilingual language learning with prevailing pedagogical assumptions. Bridges empirical research and educational practice, highlighting where evidence supports or challenges common instructional models.
      </p>
      <div class="links">
        <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DOI</a>
        <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF</a>
        <a href="projects.html#bilingual-review">Project</a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

